1
00:00:07,107 --> 00:00:08,808
I was pretty terrible just now, wasn't I?

2
00:00:09,676 --> 00:00:10,876
Actually, you did a great job.

3
00:00:12,145 --> 00:00:13,613
Come on, I know how I did.

4
00:00:14,547 --> 00:00:16,515
Look, there's no one else here,

5
00:00:16,516 --> 00:00:18,083
so you don't have to be polite.

6
00:00:18,084 --> 00:00:19,318
I feel bad for Shasha.

7
00:00:19,319 --> 00:00:21,120
Having to act with a total rookie like me.

8
00:00:21,121 --> 00:00:23,021
She's so full of herself.

9
00:00:23,022 --> 00:00:25,542
She thinks she's a lock for the
part, so she's not even trying.

10
00:00:26,426 --> 00:00:27,193
You shouldn't say that.

11
00:00:27,194 --> 00:00:28,560
Especially about someone
in your own company.

12
00:00:28,561 --> 00:00:30,229
But thanks, anyway.

13
00:00:30,230 --> 00:00:31,764
Regardless of why

14
00:00:31,765 --> 00:00:32,699
you decided to keep me around...

15
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:34,666
Even if I'm just here just for show,

16
00:00:34,667 --> 00:00:36,069
at least it's good experience.

17
00:00:37,237 --> 00:00:38,557
I don't see you like that.

18
00:00:42,976 --> 00:00:43,676
By the way,

19
00:00:43,676 --> 00:00:44,611
have you seen

20
00:00:44,611 --> 00:00:45,111
those posts online

21
00:00:45,112 --> 00:00:46,312
where people are shipping us?

22
00:00:46,679 --> 00:00:48,047
They even gave us a name...

23
00:00:48,048 --> 00:00:49,015
"Black &amp; White."

24
00:00:49,016 --> 00:00:50,116
Oh, yeah!

25
00:00:50,950 --> 00:00:51,950
People are so creative.

26
00:00:53,353 --> 00:00:54,354
So you've seen it too?

27
00:00:55,422 --> 00:00:56,322
Honestly, today

28
00:00:56,323 --> 00:00:58,243
is the first time we've
actually met one-on-one.

29
00:01:18,111 --> 00:01:19,312
How did you know...?

30
00:01:20,847 --> 00:01:22,282
That song is really beautiful.

31
00:01:22,982 --> 00:01:24,350
I actually wrote that myself.

32
00:01:24,884 --> 00:01:26,785
I've only ever performed
it on my livestreams.

33
00:01:26,786 --> 00:01:27,946
Wait, you've seen my streams?

34
00:01:30,090 --> 00:01:31,791
I was so awkward back then.

35
00:01:32,625 --> 00:01:34,293
But you're pretty impressive.

36
00:01:34,294 --> 00:01:36,054
You picked it up after
hearing it just once.

37
00:01:36,563 --> 00:01:38,331
The melody just sounds... familiar.

38
00:01:38,965 --> 00:01:40,033
Really familiar.

39
00:01:40,633 --> 00:01:42,469
Are you saying I plagiarized it?

40
00:01:43,203 --> 00:01:44,903
I told you, I wrote that myself.

41
00:01:44,904 --> 00:01:46,172
It might be a bit unpolished,

42
00:01:46,706 --> 00:01:48,340
but that doesn't mean I stole it.

43
00:01:48,341 --> 00:01:50,342
I get it, you're a "real" songwriter

44
00:01:50,343 --> 00:01:51,845
and I'm just a "dance idol."

45
00:01:52,378 --> 00:01:53,578
But let me tell you something:

46
00:01:53,947 --> 00:01:55,587
I'm not going to let you look down on me.

47
00:02:03,923 --> 00:02:05,283
Why would I ever look down on you?

48
00:02:08,761 --> 00:02:10,195
I have an idea.

49
00:02:10,196 --> 00:02:11,364
For this commercial,

50
00:02:11,931 --> 00:02:13,209
let's try something a bit bolder.

51
00:02:13,233 --> 00:02:14,873
Who says it has to be a straight romance?

52
00:02:15,201 --> 00:02:16,368
Right now, the internet

53
00:02:16,369 --> 00:02:18,103
is obsessed with BL storylines.

54
00:02:18,104 --> 00:02:19,439
"Black &amp; White"...

55
00:02:20,540 --> 00:02:21,580
I'm talking about you two.
